  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Disengagement, Disassociation, Reintegration and Reconciliation (DDRR) and Peacebuilding in the Lake Chad Basin Region and the Sahel</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme builds on previous progress made in Cameroon, Chad, Niger and Nigeria and seeks to evaluate if setting up a Disengagement, Dissassociation, Reintegration, and Reconciliation (DDRR) framework in Burkina Faso is feasible and considered beneficial. The overall programme goal is for the Governments of Cameroon, Chad, and Niger to implement by 2023 DDRR programmes for individuals who have disengaged from Boko Haram, ISWAP, Jama&apos;at Nusrat al-Islam wal-Muslimin (JNIM), Ansar al Islam and IS Greater Sahara (ISGS), as applicable, with limited donor support, while the Government of Burkina Faso evaluates whether a DDRR approach is feasible by 2023. The International Organization for Migration&#x2019;s (IOM) support is provided under country-specific objectives, while continuing its efforts to ensure regional coherence and harmonization.</narrative>
  </description>
